            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, I fixed that problem in the timespan between my last comment and now. The long-term solution would be to delegate the interpretation of `rplugin/mylang/` dirs completely to the remote host, so we can respect each language's own notion of \"module\"/\"package\"/etc. \r\n Especially for more \"static\" languages with some kind of compilation model, it might want to compile all plugins to one cached executable.",
